{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "07", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "17", "M": "02", "S": "35"}}, "news": [{"title": "Telangana government picks Singapore firm for Future City master plan", "para": "Singapore-based DP Architects has been appointed as the consultant to prepare the master plan for Telangana's Bharat Future City (BFC). The firm will develop a comprehensive plan for the 765 sq km area, with an immediate focus on 30,000 acres for land use and infrastructure, including specialized zones for life sciences, EVs, and advanced manufacturing.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/telangana-government-chooses-dp-architects-for-bharat-future-city-master-plan/131570480?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-53358/131570480.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "OC exemption for power connection extended to 2,400 sq ft buildings in Bengaluru", "para": "Bengaluru residents can now get electricity connections without Occupancy Certificates. The Karnataka government has extended this exemption to residential buildings on plots up to 2,400 sqft. This move aims to simplify access to essential services. Over four lakh buildings in Bengaluru are expected to benefit. This decision follows a Supreme Court directive.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/bengaluru-extends-power-connection-oc-exemption-for-2400-sq-ft-homes/131570366?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-63272/131570366.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Noida: Highrise fires reveal grey areas in society safety after handover is done", "para": "A recent fire in Noida's Ivy County high-rise has highlighted critical gaps in fire safety systems for tall residential buildings. Residents and experts are calling for stricter enforcement of fire norms, regular audits, and investment in modern rescue technology, as current firefighting equipment struggles to reach upper floors.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/noida-highrises-face-fire-safety-concerns-post-handover-residents-demand-stricter-regulations/131570318?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-49530/131570318.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}